  "body": "Try to read an old block (which was moved to snapshots) using standalone rpcdaemon:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl localhost:8545 \\\r\n    -X POST \\\r\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n    -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBlockByNumber\",\"params\": [\"0xE4E9A2\", false],\"id\":1}'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe following command used to work on v2022.07.04, but it is not working anymore on v2022.08.01.\r\n\r\nNote: that is for running rpcdaemon without an active erigon node, i.e., rpcdaemon + datadir only, which is useful when you just want to query historical data adhoc without having to start full sync process.\r\n\r\nRunning standalone erigon (with embedded rpcdaemon), or erigon + rpcdaemon works. The regression seems to be related just to rpcdaemon without an active erigon node. Querying recent blocks (which were not moved to snapshots) works.\r\n\r\nI was able to track down the regression to `api._blockReader.BlockWithSenders` call, apparently it is not looking for blocks in snapshots anymore in v2022.08.01.\r\n",
